000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS_PRESS_BW_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS_PRESS_BW_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS_PRESS_BW_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/SPARKS">Sparks</a>分享了新的单曲“淹死在泪水中”，并与<em>NME</em>谈到了如何不受全球政治影响的不可能，并分享了他们与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-last-dinner-party">上一场晚宴聚会</a>合作的希望。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-interviews/sparks-interview-2020-new-album-a-steady-drip-drip-drip-2663230">摇滚会杀死Braincells吗？ - 罗素·梅尔（Russell Mael），火花</a></strong></li></ul><p>罗素（Russell）和罗恩·梅尔（Ron Mael）准备发行新专辑“ Mad！” 5月2日，抒情诗人罗恩（Ron）承认，唐纳德·特朗普（Donald Trump）作为美国总统的连任一直是Sparks音乐趋势的一部分，在2020年的专辑“ A A A Be Stupped Drip，Drip，Drip”中，他们的歌曲“请不要让My World”为“请不要让我的世界”。</p><p>罗恩说：“我们对某些事情有信念，但我们并不以明确的方式表达它们。” “我们不想讲课或口号，但是如果可以以更微妙的方式完成，那么这些事件现在很难避免世界上世界上任何地方，尤其是在美国。</p><p> “您无法摆脱这种感觉。我们尽量不要直接受到外部事件的影响，但是您不禁会对您的工作产生某种影响。”</p><p> &#39;疯狂的！&#39;这是Sparks的第一张专辑，因为他们的 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sparks-announce-signing-to-transgressive-records-3804191">新标签侵犯了</a>，并在2023年的《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/sparks-the-girl-is-crying-in-her-latte-review-3446548">女孩在拿铁咖啡中哭泣</a>》之后。按照单曲“ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sparks-repeat-their-mantra-since-1972-on-single-do-things-my-own-way-announce-new-album-mad-with-uk-europe-and-japan-tour-3833179">我自己的方式做事情</a>”和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sparks-share-whimsical-single-jansport-backpack-and-reveal-mad-album-artwork-tracklist-and-release-date-3841282">“ Jansport Backpack</a> ”之后，今天看到了新的预览歌曲“淹没在眼泪之海中”的发行 - 请查看下面的视频。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="火花 - 淹没在泪水中（官方视频）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ODeoz3pDgNU?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> &#39;疯狂的！&#39;紧随其后的是在其<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sparks-new-musical-x-crucior-3342665">第二部电影</a><em>X Crucior上工作的火花。</em>由约翰·沃（John Woo）执导的是<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/annette-review-adam-driver-3036925">2021年的音乐剧<em>安妮特（Annette）</em></a> ，该音乐剧由亚当·司机（Adam Driver）和马里恩·科蒂拉德（Marion Cotillard）主演。这也是在埃德加·赖特（Edgar Wright）备受赞誉和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/the-sparks-brothers-wins-best-music-film-at-the-bandlab-nme-awards-2022-3172621">NME屡获殊荣的</a>2021年纪录片<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/the-sparks-brothers-review-edgar-wright-2873882"><em>《 Sparks Brothers》</em></a>之后。</p><p>在下面查看我们的完整采访，以了解Sparks对“完全不同的” <em>X十字的暗示，</em>他们最终如何将吉他独奏纳入他们的音乐中，以及他们对最后一场晚餐聚会的二重奏的希望， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-the-last-dinner-partys-spirited-cover-of-sparks-classic-this-town-aint-big-enough-for-the-both-of-us-3605971">他们去年对我们俩都不够大。</a></p><p> <strong>NME：嗨，罗恩和罗素。 &#39;疯狂的！&#39;似乎是Sparks的出色专辑标题。你们俩都很生气吗？</strong></p><p><strong>罗素·梅尔（Russell Mael）：</strong> “这很适合这张专辑，这也是因为我们经常被描述为疯狂的含义：疯狂和生气。&#39;疯了！&#39;适合该描述，也适合这些时代，当一切都感觉完全失控时，这个词的各种含义都会发疯。</p><p> “有很长的火花董事会会议：&#39;我们真的需要标题中的感叹号吗？&#39;我们认为绝对需要重点回家。”</p><p><strong>是什么让您决定签署此唱片的侵犯？</strong></p><p><strong>鲁塞尔（Rusell）：</strong> “他们是火花的粉丝，更重要的是，这张新专辑的粉丝。这是一个唱片公司，人们只是喜欢音乐，而这与会计有关。</p><p> “锦上添花是&#39;我自己做的事情&#39;。 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/transgressive-records-interview-20-years-foals-arlo-parks-sophie-how-to-advice-3814023">这是他们20年来标签的咒语</a>。它也与他们共鸣，将其作为我们的第一首宣言歌曲作为我们的第一首单曲。”</p><p><strong>火花的宣言也有多少是“我自己的方式”？</strong></p><p><strong>拉塞尔：</strong> “我们没有带着一个小徽章，说我们已经做了55年了，但对于这张唱片来说，这似乎是一个不错的开场白。</p><p> “从第一天起，这一直是我们不言而喻的咒语。我们为保持火花宇宙而没有屈服或偏离路线而感到自豪。不要屈服于外部影响，这使Sparks在这段长期的职业中保持了纯净的态度。”</p><p><strong>罗恩·梅尔（Ron Mael</strong> ）：“我们真的很幸运，我们被鼓励尽早遵循这条路线。 </p><figure id="attachment_3833181" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3833181" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3833181" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/sparks@2000x1270.jpg" alt="火花，2025年" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/sparks@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/sparks@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/sparks@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/sparks@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/sparks@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/sparks@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3833181" class="wp-caption-text"> Sparks，2025年。信用：Munachi Osegbu</figcaption></figure><p><strong>新的单曲“淹没在眼泪中”的抒情听起来异常直截了当的关系戏剧……</strong></p><p> <strong>Ron:</strong> “We don&#39;t usually get inspired by anything that&#39;s happened in a relationship context, and it wasn&#39;t inspired by any particular incident.</p><p> “I hate to use the term &#39;sincerity&#39;, because we&#39;re sincere about everything we write. But we wanted to write something from a more traditional feeling of what a pop song should be, lyrically. A few songs on this album were inspired by that.”</p><p> <strong>Speaking of being traditional, this album even features a guitar solo, on the closing song &#39;Lord Have Mercy&#39;. That must be a first for Sparks?</strong></p><p> <strong>Ron:</strong> “I know! Don&#39;t hate us for it.”</p><p> <strong>Russell:</strong> “We have stuck it at the end of the album. We&#39;re not a guitar-hero-worshipping band, but there is the right time and place for a good solo. A blistering solo under the grandeur of that song felt an appropriate way to close it.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Sparks - JanSport Backpack (Official Lyric Video)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/oEEIU-WrorY?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> <strong>Have you heard from JanSport about your &#39;JanSport Backpack&#39; single?</strong></p><p> <strong>Ron:</strong> “We&#39;re waiting for either a lawsuit or an endorsement deal. Either is expected.”</p><p> <strong>The song &#39;My Devotion&#39; describes irrational obsessions. Does that apply to either of you?</strong></p><p> <strong>Ron:</strong> “Both of us are devoted to sumo wrestling. If you take it on the surface, sumo is this antiquated fat guy thing, but really, it&#39;s beautiful. Like with any sport, if you keep watching, you get an attachment to certain key people and we do start rooting for various wrestlers. If you get into it, you can get really sucked in.</p><p> “People always say Japanese audiences are more restrained but, having been to a sumo match, they can be wild about some things.” </p><figure id="attachment_3851274" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3851274" style="width: 1333px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3851274" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS-2025_press_CREDIT-MUNACHI-OSEGBU_2000.jpg" alt="Sparks, 2025. Credit: Munachi Osegbu" width="1333" height="2000" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS-2025_press_CREDIT-MUNACHI-OSEGBU_2000.jpg 1333w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS-2025_press_CREDIT-MUNACHI-OSEGBU_2000-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS-2025_press_CREDIT-MUNACHI-OSEGBU_2000-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS-2025_press_CREDIT-MUNACHI-OSEGBU_2000-696x1044.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/SPARKS-2025_press_CREDIT-MUNACHI-OSEGBU_2000-1068x1602.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1333px) 100vw, 1333px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3851274" class="wp-caption-text"> Sparks, 2025. Credit: Munachi Osegbu</figcaption></figure><p> <strong>How has John Woo come to direct your next film, <em>X Crucior</em> ?</strong></p><p> <strong>Russell:</strong> “After <em>Annette</em> , we wanted to do another movie musical that channels what we do, without it just being another Sparks album. John Woo said in an interview that he&#39;d never done a musical, which we were astounded by. We&#39;re fans of his, so about a year ago we approached him with our idea. He heard the whole two hours of what will be the film and said: &#39;I love this, let&#39;s do it&#39;. We now have some great producers working on it and it&#39;s hopefully going into production soon-ish.”</p><p> <strong>What can you say about the plot?</strong></p><p> <strong>Russell:</strong> “Story-wise, it&#39;s 180 degrees away from <em>Annette</em> . It&#39;s totally different from <em>Annette</em> , a really different genre, but it still has all the idiosyncrasies that come with Sparks&#39; sensibilities.”</p><p> <strong>Ron:</strong> “It&#39;s all singing, no dialogue. Singing is a natural thing in the world that&#39;s being pictured in <em>X Crucior</em> .”</p><p> <strong>Russell:</strong> “We bonded with John over <em>The Umbrellas Of Cherbourg</em> . It&#39;s one of our favourite films, and one of his, and that&#39;s all sung too.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="The Last Dinner Party - This Town Ain’t Big Enough For Both Of Us [On The Road]" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/MVW5h7ZGRRI?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> <strong>What did you think of The Last Dinner Party&#39;s cover of &#39;This Town Ain&#39;t Big Enough For The Both Of Us&#39;?</strong></p><p> <strong>Russell:</strong> “It&#39;s really good. They&#39;ve raised the key and sing it higher than Sparks, if you can believe that. If they ever duet with us on that song, they&#39;ll have to meet us halfway.”</p><p> <strong>Ron:</strong> “We still play it in the original key, though.”</p><p> <strong>Russell</strong> : “That&#39;s true. If anyone can do the last note in our key, they get an award.”</p><p> <strong>Would you ever work with them?</strong></p><p> <strong>Russell:</strong> “I saw them in LA and went backstage. When I left, it was: &#39;Hey, let&#39;s do something together!&#39; from both sides. Those things usually don&#39;t end up happening, but let&#39;s see. I think they&#39;re really good, and a song with them would be fun. They seemed genuine about doing something, and I genuinely think it&#39;d be cool to do something together too.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Do Things My Own Way" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UT-ad9MqsKQ?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Sparks&#39; new album &#39;MAD!&#39; is released on May 2 via Transgressive. They&#39;ll also be touring this summer. See the full list of dates below and <a href="https://www.ticketmaster.co.uk/sparks-tickets/artist/736168?irgwc=1&amp;utm_source=2862475-NME%20Networks%20Media%20Limited&amp;utm_medium=affiliate&amp;utm_campaign=2862475&amp;awtrc=&amp;clickId=xOnTBHWu7xyKRF4SKGSfxVZQUksyxcWqzXxF0U0&amp;camefrom=CFC_BUYAT_2862475&amp;ircid=7559" target="_blank" rel="noopener">visit here for tickets</a> and more information.</p><p><strong>六月<br />8 – ROHM Theatre, Kyoto</strong><br /> <strong>10 – Zepp Namba, Osaka</strong><br /> <strong>12-13 – Ex Theater Roppongi, Tokyo</strong><br /> <strong>19-20 – Eventim Hammersmith Apollo, London</strong><br /> <strong>21-22 – O2 Apollo, Manchester</strong><br /> <strong>24 – Royal Concert Hall, Glasgow</strong><br /> <strong>26 – PHIL, Haarlem</strong><br /> <strong>28 – Cirque Royal, Brussels</strong><br /> <strong>30 – Salle Playel, Paris</strong></p><p><strong>七月</strong><br /><strong>1 – Gloria, Cologne</strong><br /> <strong>3 – DR Koncerthuset, Copenhagen</strong><br /> <strong>4 – Grona Lund Tivoli, Stockholm</strong><br /> <strong>6 – Uber Eats Music Hall, Berlin</strong><br /> <strong>8 – Teatro Degli Arcimboldi, Milan</strong><br /> <strong>12 – BBK Live 2025, Bilbao</strong><br /> <strong>15-16 – National Stadium, Dublin</strong><br /> <strong>18 – Playhouse, Edinburgh</strong><br /> <strong>19 – The Halls, Wolverhampton</strong></p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sparks-interview-mad-the-last-dinner-party-donald-trump-john-woo-x-crucior-3851250">Sparks tell us about new album &#39;Mad!&#39;, Trump&#39;s America, and dreams of working with The Last Dinner Party</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
